WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the Apple A19 Pro SoC, manufactured on
TSMC's third-generation 3nm (N3P) process. It defines the 6-core Apple GPU
with 128 stream processors and integrated Neural Accelerator, the 16-core
Neural Engine, the CPU performance and efficiency core cluster, and the
MetalFX upscaling inference pipeline.

WHY IT EXISTS
The A19 Pro powers iPhone 17 Pro, delivering 40+ TOPS of on-device AI
compute and GPU performance approaching M2. GIOP models its silicon as
formulas so that MetalFX upscaling and Neural Engine-assisted auto-grade
become predictable, auditable operations.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Multi-Core Scaling (Amdahl):
  P(N) = 1 / ( (1 - f_parallel) + f_parallel / N )
  where f_parallel = 0.93, N = 6 (2 performance + 4 efficiency). Single-
  core Geekbench 6 ≈ 3,950; multi-core ≈ 10,800. 50% larger L2 cache versus
  A18 Pro reduces cache miss rate by ~18%.[reference:4]

GPU Compute (Apple-designed, 6 cores, 128 stream processors):
  TFLOPS_FP16 = (cores * ALUs_per_core * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
  = (6 * 128 * 2 * 1.45e9) / 1e12 ≈ 2.2 TFLOPS
  Neural Accelerator integrated into GPU delivers ~4× AI compute versus
  A18 Pro for matrix multiplication workloads.[reference:5]

Neural Engine (16-core):
  TOPS_INT8 = (MAC_units * 2 * f_neural) / 1e12
  ≈ (16 * 1024 * 2 * 2.0e9) / 1e12 ≈ 65 TOPS (peak)
  Sustained AI throughput ≈ 40 TOPS under thermal constraint. Optimized
  for transformer attention (GPT, Stable Diffusion on-device).[reference:6]

MetalFX Upscaling:
  Latency per frame at 1080p → 4K ≈ 4.2 ms (measured on MetalFX Temporal).
  The upscaler uses a lightweight CNN running on the Neural Engine.

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR5x-8533, 64-bit):
  BW = 8 * 8.533e9 * 2 = 136.5 GB/s

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- iPhone 17 Pro / Pro Max, iPad mini 8, Apple TV 4K (2026).
- GIOP MetalFX upscaling, on-device AI grading, spatial computing.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers optimizing iOS/macOS GIOP runtimes; L3 Colorists previewing
Apple device-specific ODTs.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Models the A19 Pro's GPU and Neural Engine as formulas so that MetalFX
latency and AI grading throughput can be predicted exactly for any frame
size and bit depth.

